From: beasley@c0227.ae.ge.com
Subject: lpd problem solved
Date: 28 Nov 93 23:16:57 GMT

I've seen many complaints that lpd wont stay active.  At least on my system
the problem was solved by creating the directory /usr/spool/lpd

lpd aparently wanted to create a lock file 'lpd.lock' there and if the
directory didnt exist he died.

I made this discovery by looking in /var/logs/notice (this is where
syslogd puts his messages) there were many complaints from lpd that
then file /usr/spool/lpd/lpd.lock didnt exist, also several complaints
that a filter i had specified in /etc/printcap didnt exist either.

check /etc/syslog.conf for where syslogd writes output, it may be different
than
mine

hope this helps.

mike beasley@ae.ge.com

