From: norman@flaubert.bellcore.com (Norman Ramsey)
Subject: Re: LGX Bug List #4
Date: 29 Nov 93 02:25:17 GMT

> [04] : Some manual pages are in the incorrect format or the man command is
>       not expecting all possible formats :-

I have a fix for the manual-page problem, but mail to Ian Parkin
bounces.  The man pages are just fine; there's a bug in man (returning
a pointer to an automatic array).  This patch to man-1.1 fixes it:

*** man.c.dist  Sat Aug 24 18:01:03 1991
--- man.c       Thu Nov 25 16:07:44 1993
***************
*** 715,722 ****
       char *path;
  {
    FILE *fp;
!   char buf[BUFSIZ];
!   char ult[BUFSIZ];
    char *beg;
    char *end;
  
--- 715,722 ----
       char *path;
  {
    FILE *fp;
!   static char buf[BUFSIZ];
!   static char ult[BUFSIZ];
    char *beg;
    char *end;
  

