Crossposted-To: comp.windows.x.pex,comp.os.linux.help
From: harada@ka2sho.mis.hiroshima-u.ac.jp (HARADA Koichi)
Subject: Re: linux and pex
Date: Mon, 29 Nov 1993 01:52:07 GMT

Friedrich Fahnert (fahnert@informatik.hu-berlin.de) wrote:

> I have installed at home the latest SLS release of 
> Linux and I was wondering if and how it would be 
> possible to install pex on my computer.  Would I
> need  an entire new X-server?  Where can I get 
> a linux port of PEX?

If you get XFree86-1.3 binary for Linux, then PEX is already included.
If you downloaded XFree86-2.0, you need to re-make server to include PEX.
All informations are in the docs of XFree86.  Get them first. 

